<h2>Relative to the parent</h2>

<p>Width and height utilities are generated from the utility API. Includes support for <code>25%</code>, <code>50%</code>, <code>75%</code>, <code>100%</code>, and <code>auto</code> by default. Modify those values as you need to generate different utilities here.</p>

{% snippet %}
<div class="stack-v">
  <div class="w-25 docs-box">25%</div>
  <div class="w-50 docs-box">50%</div>
  <div class="w-75 docs-box">75%</div>
  <div class="w-100 docs-box">100%</div>
  <div class="w-auto docs-box">auto</div>
</div>
{% endsnippet %}

<h2>Relative to the viewport</h2>

<p>You can also use utilities to set the width and height relative to the viewport.</p>

{% highlight %}
<div class="vw-100">Width: 100vw</div>
<div class="vh-100">Height: 100vh</div>
<div class="min-vh-100">Min-height: 100vh</div>
{% endhighlight %}
